@edition "2026.6"

-- D1(xxii) frontier guardrail. This program is VALID (it type-checks clean — a `_test`,
-- not a `_bad`), but it uses the PROP-WITH operator (`e ?: alt` — unwrap an `Ok` payload, or
-- evaluate the fallback `alt` on anything else). eval yields the `Ok` payload or evaluates
-- `alt` (a PURE conditional — no early-return, unlike `?`); the compute spine has no prop-with
-- lowering — `normComp`/`norm` reach the `PropWith` AST node and refuse it (the `default` arm
-- of `normComp`). The differential harness must report it `unsupported` — a CLEAN refusal at
-- the compiler frontier, never a miscompile.
--
-- This is the backend-slice analogue of a `_bad` twin: a backend slice adds no checker
-- rejection rule, so the guarantee under test is "the compiler refuses what it cannot
-- yet lower, loudly", asserted by the harness rather than by an error count. D1(ii)
-- moved the frontier PAST scalar `match`; D1(iii) PAST tuples; D1(iv) PAST ADT
-- constructors; D1(v) PAST records; D1(vi) PAST lists; D1(vii) PAST closures-as-values;
-- D1(viii) PAST first-class `def` references; D1(ix) PAST first-class BUILTIN references;
-- D1(x) PAST short-circuit `&&`/`||`; D1(xi) PAST non-tail `if` as a value; D1(xii) PAST
-- non-tail `match` as a value; D1(xiii) PAST multi-clause `def`s; D1(xiv) PAST reassignment;
-- D1(xv) PAST atom literals; D1(xvi) PAST duration literals; D1(xvii) PAST `for`
-- comprehensions; D1(xviii) PAST integer ranges; D1(xix) PAST index assignment; D1(xx) PAST
-- the `loop` construct; D1(xxi) PAST type tests; D1(xxii) PAST the PROPAGATE operator (`e?` —
-- unwrap-or-early-return on Result; see compile_propagate_test). The frontier now sits at the
-- PROP-WITH operator (`e ?: alt`). This file uses one, so it still refuses; when prop-with
-- lowers (a later D1 slice, an Ok-payload-or-fallback select), it flips from `unsupported` to
-- a print with no edit.

def parsePos(n: Number): Result(Number, String)
  if n > 0 then Ok(n) else Error("neg")

def orZero(n: Number): Number
  parsePos(n) ?: 0

def main(): Effect [io] ()
  println(orZero(5))
  println(orZero(-3))
